{"title":"9.B2-2025","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/9.B2-2025.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"# Curvas ROC en\\NInvestigación Clínica","guid":"VCAyrlQ_MxMdSHSeFJYMSA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"## Conceptos básicos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"- ROC = Receiver Operating Characteristic curve","guid":"NZPzLywNl0Z4xcIfGpdcfA","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"- Método estadístico para determinar exactitud diagnóstica de tests con escalas continuas","guid":"dBWGChmwlmknMzjkVtExfA","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"- Aplicable a tests que reportan resultados cuantitativos","guid":"Qo61KkqahlN_HfF8d0ELUQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"5","parent":"0","text":"## Propósitos\\Nespecíficos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"- Determinar punto de corte con mayor sensibilidad y especificidad","guid":"I_h7gUI8yFgrN4Y2YDwn4w","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"5","text":"- Evaluar capacidad discriminativa del test","guid":"CZ9_32d-smhWle5LQ6BQTw","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"5","text":"- Comparar capacidad discriminativa de dos o más tests","guid":"OvsSkTI6J-1p97pWDxtFPw","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"0","text":"## Construcción\\Nde curva ROC","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"- Eje Y: Sensibilidad","guid":"BnlbAQdALvQjsVGHcZBUkQ","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"9","text":"- Eje X: 1-Especificidad","guid":"NgeuKwG_qa94NnBBa5uhWg","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"9","text":"- Ambos ejes incluyen valores entre 0 y 1 (0% a 100%)","guid":"Lc1A9XD8MmAGMv3XIeLG_w","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"9","text":"- Diagonal de referencia: línea desde punto 0,0 al punto 1,1 (línea de no-discriminación)","guid":"CqzIyS1mNrt4s_h8TTt98w","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"9","text":"- Se construye uniendo puntos de corte de la escala continua","guid":"eAC9D3fR6fhEfIlFG_k4kA","children":[]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"0","text":"## Categorías\\Ndiagnósticas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"- Verdaderos Positivos (VP): Estándar de oro positivo y test positivo","guid":"Og6yUG-0D3t8NWB0Q64yMA","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"15","text":"- Falsos Negativos (FN): Estándar de oro positivo y test negativo","guid":"VzLB41LLTr8HToJ_Ei3UdA","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"15","text":"- Verdaderos Negativos (VN): Estándar de oro negativo y test negativo","guid":"BQV2rXFGPNUhSRmzC37Rrg","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"15","text":"- Falsos Positivos (FP): Estándar de oro negativo y test positivo","guid":"eIZryUT6azt9DyY_Lo4Z9A","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"15","text":"- Sensibilidad = VP/(VP+FN)","guid":"RroU6nVFloEaKbtPdIdV4A","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"15","text":"- Especificidad = VN/(FP+VN)","guid":"ZkHI4SBcuSYWahzfcO6Rqw","children":[]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"0","text":"## Punto de\\Ncorte óptimo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"- Mayor índice de Youden = (sensibilidad + especificidad - 1)","guid":"TcLv4Q8eFVs-Kg-eRcOs8A","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"- Gráficamente: punto más cercano al ángulo superior-izquierdo (punto 0,1)","guid":"Bu__UwKmmONhvOWBQP6xpA","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"22","text":"- Determina sensibilidad y especificidad más alta conjuntamente","guid":"clqoXl3yRfUErOPUSY1qQg","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"22","text":"- En algunos casos se prefiere maximizar solo sensibilidad (tamizaje) o especificidad (confirmación)","guid":"ML2UtAv7ZlNbuz62NcMLYQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"0","text":"## Capacidad\\Ndiscriminativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"0","text":"- Medida a través del área\\Nbajo la curva ROC (AUC -\\NArea Under the Curve)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"0","text":"- AUC: parámetro independiente de la\\Nprevalencia de la enfermedad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"- AUC = 0,50: test\\Nno-discriminativo (coincide\\Ncon línea de\\Nno-discriminación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"0","text":"- AUC = 1,00: test\\Ndiagnóstico perfecto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"0","text":"- Mayor AUC = mayor\\Ncapacidad discriminativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"0","text":"- AUC es un estimador muestral\\N→ necesario reportar intervalos de\\Nconfianza (IC 95%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"0","text":"## Comparación de\\Ntests diagnósticos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"0","text":"- Prerrequisitos\\Nmetodológicos:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"0","text":"- Tests medidos\\Nsimultáneamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"0","text":"- Aplicados sobre\\Nmismos sujetos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"0","text":"- Contrastados contra\\Nmismo estándar de oro","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"0","text":"- Comparar AUC estadísticamente\\N(no solo numéricamente)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"0","text":"- Métodos de comparación: Hanley &\\NMcNeil o DeLong (preferido)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"0","text":"##\\NConsideraciones\\Nfinales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"0","text":"- Sensibilidad, especificidad y\\NAUC son estimadores\\Nmuestrales → reportar IC 95%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"0","text":"- Evaluar validez\\Nmetodológica del estudio\\Nbase","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"0","text":"- Uso de curvas ROC trasciende\\Nárea de tests diagnósticos (modelos\\Nde regresión logística)","guid":"","children":[]}]},"node_count":44,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"9.B2-2025","id":"map_695","resolved_references":[]}